(ATHO ROAD MAP: MAKE THE CLIENT FULLY ONE-CLICK) Tj
T*
(================================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Purpose) Tj
T*
(-------) Tj
T*
(Make Atho usable in two modes from one codebase:) Tj
T*
(1\) Non-technical mode: open app, click start, node runs in background, no terminal.) Tj
T*
(2\) Technical mode: full CLI/terminal control with same backend behavior.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Target End State) Tj
T*
(----------------) Tj
T*
(- User installs Atho desktop app.) Tj
T*
(- User opens app.) Tj
T*
(- First-run wizard sets network + role + storage path + optional bootstrap.) Tj
T*
(- App starts local control service and selected node role\(s\) automatically.) Tj
T*
(- GUI manages everything \(start/stop/restart, status, peers, sync, mining, logs\).) Tj
T*
(- Advanced users can still use terminal/VS Code/CLI with same control API.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Design Rules) Tj
T*
(------------) Tj
T*
(1\) One source of truth for process management.) Tj
T*
(2\) GUI and CLI call the same internal API.) Tj
T*
(3\) Secure by default \(local bind, auth, HMAC, least privilege\).) Tj
T*
(4\) Fail closed on critical security drift in production mode.) Tj
T*
(5\) Installer includes all runtime dependencies.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
